The paper focuses on building genealogy trees for the Brazilian research community using data from the Lattes Platform, which is a platform for managing information about individual researchers and research groups in Brazil. This involves analyzing the academic background and mentorship of researchers, which falls under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
